      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2015-12-01</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-12-17T16:35:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Department of Veterans Affairs Emergency Medical Staffing Recruitment and Retention Act</strong></p> <p>This bill authorizes the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to modify the hours of employment for a full-time VA physician or physician assistant to be more than or less than 80 hours in a biweekly pay period if the total of such employee's hours of employment in a calendar year does not exceed 2,080 hours.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-12-01T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <versionCode>17</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2016-11-14</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Reported to House with amendment(s)</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-12-28T16:34:34Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Department of Veterans Affairs Emergency Medical Staffing Recruitment and Retention Act</strong></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill authorizes the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to modify the hours of employment for a full-time VA physician or physician assistant to be more than or less than 80 hours in a biweekly pay period if the total of such employee's hours of employment in a calendar year does not exceed 2,080 hours.</p> <p> A physician or physician assistant may not accrue overtime by reason of such modified hours of employment. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-11-14T14:58:28Z</updateDate>
          <name>Reported to House with amendment(s)</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <versionCode>36</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2016-12-06</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-03-02T15:56:22Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Department of Veterans Affairs Emergency Medical Staffing Recruitment and Retention Act </strong></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill authorizes the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA), upon the advanced written request of a covered physician, to modify the hours of employment for a full-time VA physician to be more than or less than 80 hours in a biweekly pay period.</p> <p>For purpose of determining pay, such a physician shall be deemed to have a biweekly employment schedule of 80 hours. </p> <p>A physician with an irregular work schedule must account for at least 2,080 employment hours (through work or use of leave or paid time off) in a calendar year. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-12-06T20:01:19Z</updateDate>
          <name>Passed House amended</name>
        </item>
